-- Argentine Stocks: Siderar, Transportadora de Gas del Norte, YPF
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-07-12T21:31:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-12/argentine-stocks-siderar-transportadora-de-gas-del-norte-ypf.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the close in Buenos
Aires. The  Merval (MERVAL)  index fell 0.5 percent to 2,350.96.  Siderar SAIC (ERAR)   retreated 3 percent to 1.6 pesos,
its lowest price in four weeks. Argentina’s largest steel
producer fell in line with base metal prices amid signs that the
global slowdown is worsening and after the  Federal Reserve 
damped speculation for further stimulus.  Transportadora de Gas del Norte SA  (TGNO4 AF) advanced 9.8
percent to 0.483 peso, its biggest increase in nine weeks. The
Argentine natural gas transporter began an offer to exchange
$345 million in bonds for new debt and cash.  YPF SA (YPFD)   fell 1.4 percent to 82.40 pesos.
Argentina’s largest oil company retreated after crude fell
earlier today in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
